     # notekit
     
     Small Python helpers for turning plain notes into reusable text fragments.
    +
    +## Available helpers
    +
    +- `normalize_note(text)`: trims leading and trailing whitespace and collapses
    +  internal whitespace runs to single spaces.
    +- `render_checklist(items)`: normalizes each item, drops empty items, and
    +  renders the rest as a markdown checklist.
    +- `build_summary(title, lines)`: normalizes the heading and each line, rejects
    +  blank titles, drops empty lines, and returns only the heading if no
    +  non-empty lines remain.
    +
    +## Usage
    +
    +Package-root imports are supported for the public helpers:
    +
    +```python
    +from src.notekit import build_summary, normalize_note, render_checklist
    +
    +note = normalize_note("  hello   world  ")
    +checklist = render_checklist([" first task ", "  ", "second\titem"])
